  schema:name "Chatham Capitol Theatre"@en,
    "Chatham Capitol Theatre";
  schema:url <https://www.cktheatres.ca>;
  <http://www.ebu.ch/metadata/ontologies/ebucore/ebucore#hasAgentBiography> """The Chatham Capitol Theatre is a vibrant 1,208-seat entertainment gem located at 238 King Street West in the lively downtown Chatham, Ontario. This beloved venue is the go-to spot for concerts and events, attracting both national and international touring artists.

Originally a bustling movie theatre from the 1930s, the Capitol Theatre boasts beautiful Art Deco details, gilded decor, charming opera boxes, and a stunning ornate ceiling, all of which add to its historical charm.

The theatre features 756 seats on the orchestra level and 452 seats in the balcony, which can be closed off for a cozier performance atmosphere. With a 65-foot fly tower and state-of-the-art rigging, it can host large-scale, technically impressive productions. The orchestra pit is designed for optimal acoustics and can be adjusted to floor or stage level to enhance your experience."""@en;
  wikidata_property:\/P8860 "866337058" .

